WEBVTT

00:07.940 --> 00:11.120
Hi there, welcome to
this video where we

00:11.120 --> 00:12.920
are going to learn
about using privacy

00:12.920 --> 00:16.340
settings in digital
environments.

00:16.340 --> 00:18.340
The goal of the
presentation is to

00:18.340 --> 00:20.740
help you to know what
privacy settings are

00:20.740 --> 00:23.380
and how you can make
mindful choices when

00:23.380 --> 00:26.660
you use social media
applications.

00:26.660 --> 00:29.100
In the video, firstly, 
we will look at what

00:29.100 --> 00:32.420
social media is.
Following this,

00:32.420 --> 00:34.480
we will explore what
privacy settings are

00:34.480 --> 00:37.660
on social media apps.
Finally, we will

00:37.660 --> 00:39.660
consider how we can
make mindful choices

00:39.660 --> 00:41.580
about our privacy settings.

00:45.140 --> 00:47.400
People in today's
world spend a lot of time

00:47.400 --> 00:51.140
using digital
devices. Computers,

00:51.140 --> 00:53.280
smartphones and
tablets are examples

00:53.280 --> 00:55.560
of digital devices
that make up the

00:55.560 --> 00:58.580
digital environment
around us.

00:58.580 --> 01:00.720
Digital devices can 
help us through social media

01:00.720 --> 01:02.780
applications to
connect with family

01:02.780 --> 01:05.780
and friends. 
For example, we send

01:05.780 --> 01:08.800
messages and photos
using messaging apps.

01:09.860 --> 01:12.080
Which social media
applications do you

01:12.080 --> 01:13.840
or your family use?

01:19.200 --> 01:21.320
Privacy settings can
be found on every

01:21.320 --> 01:23.260
social media
application and are

01:23.260 --> 01:25.100
designed to give
users the ability to

01:25.100 --> 01:27.700
decide who can see
their online profile,

01:27.700 --> 01:30.280
what content people
can see on their

01:30.280 --> 01:32.580
profile and if people
have the ability to

01:32.580 --> 01:35.440
contact them, for
example, call them 

01:35.440 --> 01:39.760
or send an instant message.

01:39.760 --> 01:41.300
Different social media
platforms have different

01:41.300 --> 01:43.320
privacy settings, therefore

01:43.320 --> 01:45.840
it is important to be
mindful when you sign

01:45.840 --> 01:47.580
up to a new
application

01:47.580 --> 01:49.740
and double check that 
the privacy settings are

01:49.740 --> 01:51.880
going to enable you
to have control over

01:51.880 --> 01:53.820
who is able to see
your online content

01:53.820 --> 01:56.860
or not. Most
applications allow

01:56.860 --> 01:58.760
you to have 
a publicly open profile

01:58.760 --> 02:01.320
where everyone using
the platform can see

02:01.320 --> 02:03.580
your personal information.

02:03.580 --> 02:06.140
For example, a personal
photo of you, your status

02:06.140 --> 02:08.360
and other information about you

02:08.360 --> 02:10.900
such as age, gender,
where you go to

02:10.900 --> 02:14.020
school. Whilst it is
nice to share photos

02:14.020 --> 02:16.280
and your status with
family and friends,

02:16.280 --> 02:18.720
consider whether you
want all users of the

02:18.720 --> 02:21.140
social media platform
to see these things.

02:21.640 --> 02:23.780
Most applications
track the internet

02:23.780 --> 02:25.880
address or position
to reveal your

02:25.880 --> 02:28.200
location, sometimes
showing the exact

02:28.200 --> 02:31.100
address. Whilst it
might be a good idea

02:31.100 --> 02:32.820
to share your
location with family

02:32.820 --> 02:35.120
members, it is not
recommended to reveal

02:35.120 --> 02:37.180
it to everyone using
the social media

02:37.180 --> 02:40.220
platform. You might
also want to consider

02:40.220 --> 02:41.740
whether this is
something you need to

02:41.740 --> 02:44.240
share with some 
of your friends.

02:44.240 --> 02:46.420
For example, maybe you 
do not want all your

02:46.420 --> 02:47.680
friends to see that you have

02:47.680 --> 02:50.380
an appointment with 
a doctor. We see that

02:50.380 --> 02:52.620
influencers on social
media post to the

02:52.620 --> 02:55.100
whole world to gain
followers, exchanging

02:55.100 --> 02:56.820
their personal privacy 
for the money gain.

02:56.820 --> 03:00.320
However, we
should avoid posting

03:00.320 --> 03:02.180
everything to the
whole world and

03:02.180 --> 03:04.100
carefully consider
our privacy settings

03:04.100 --> 03:06.840
when using social
media applications.

03:09.040 --> 03:11.000
Here are some
examples of questions

03:11.000 --> 03:12.540
you might ask
yourself when setting

03:12.540 --> 03:15.680
up a new application.
Do I want my teachers

03:15.680 --> 03:17.940
at school to see
videos I post with my

03:17.940 --> 03:20.560
friends? Do I want to
be messaged

03:20.560 --> 03:22.800
by anybody using the
social media platform

03:22.800 --> 03:24.740
or only people who
are in my phone

03:24.740 --> 03:27.120
contact list? Do I
want complete

03:27.120 --> 03:29.380
strangers to see my
summer holiday photos?

03:29.380 --> 03:31.940
Do I want anybody
to see where I am

03:31.940 --> 03:35.540
located on the map
anytime? Be mindful.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.380
Who do you want to
give access to your

03:37.380 --> 03:40.260
online content? You
can think about this

03:40.260 --> 03:42.280
and maybe discuss it
with a parent before

03:42.280 --> 03:44.020
checking the privacy
settings of any

03:44.020 --> 03:49.300
applications that you
have. One thing to

03:49.300 --> 03:51.120
consider is that even
if you have control

03:51.120 --> 03:53.560
over your own privacy
settings, others that

03:53.560 --> 03:55.660
you share content
with might not have

03:55.660 --> 03:57.840
control over their
privacy settings.

03:58.020 --> 04:00.180
This can lead to
content about you

04:00.180 --> 04:02.400
being shared more
widely via someone

04:02.400 --> 04:05.700
else's social media
applications.

04:05.700 --> 04:08.120
Be mindful. Check your
own privacy settings

04:08.120 --> 04:10.280
and inform others of
your right to choose

04:10.280 --> 04:12.500
what content about
you is shared via

04:12.500 --> 04:16.480
their online platforms. 
So in this

04:16.480 --> 04:19.540
short video we learnt
that: We are part of

04:19.540 --> 04:21.320
the digital
environment when we

04:21.320 --> 04:24.020
are using social
media applications.

04:24.420 --> 04:26.300
Privacy settings are
designed to give

04:26.300 --> 04:28.960
users the ability to
decide who can see

04:28.960 --> 04:31.580
their online profile,
what content people

04:31.580 --> 04:33.520
can see on their
profile, and if

04:33.520 --> 04:35.180
people have the
ability to contact

04:35.180 --> 04:38.780
them or not. We can
be mindful and make

04:38.780 --> 04:40.340
good choices about
these privacy

04:40.340 --> 04:43.040
settings by asking
ourselves, who do I

04:43.040 --> 04:46.040
want to give access
to my online content?

04:48.020 --> 04:50.080
Thank you for watching! 

04:50.080 --> 04:52.200
To learn more about 
digital environments and

04:52.200 --> 04:54.920
digital citizenship,
watch other videos in out series.